              {partition.switchCost.toFixed(1)}
            </div>
            <div className="text-xs text-slate-400">{partition.switches} × 5%</div>
          </div>
          <div className="text-center">
            <div className="text-slate-400 text-xs mb-1">Imbalance Cost</div>
            <div className="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">
              {partition.imbalanceCost.toFixed(1)}
            </div>
            <div className="text-xs text-slate-400">waste</div>
          </div>
          <div className="text-center">
            <div className="text-slate-400 text-xs mb-1">Market Efficiency</div>
            <div className={`text-xl font-bold ${
              partition.marketEfficiency > 90 ? 'text-green-400' : 
              partition.marketEfficiency > 80 ? 'text-yellow-400' : 'text-red-400'
            }`}>
              {partition.marketEfficiency.toFixed(1)}%
            </div>
            <div className="text-xs text-slate-400">productive</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Explanation */}
      <div className="mt-6 p-4 bg-purple-500/10 border border-purple-400/30 rounded-lg">
        <p className="text-sm text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          <strong className="text-purple-300">The Brain's Internal Economy:</strong> Each token has a computational 
          cost (shown in badges). The orchestrator allocates work between two specialized producers—LLM A 
          (creative/intuitive) and LLM B (analytical/structured)—trying to maintain a target α ratio. 
          Market constraints prevent mid-sentence switches (coherence rules). Switches cost 5% overhead 
          (context-switching tax). Imbalance creates waste. Market efficiency shows how well the brain 
          allocates its computational resources.
        </p>
        <p className="text-sm text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          <strong className="text-green-300">⚡ Greedy:</strong> Makes locally optimal choices at each sentence 
          boundary. Fast but can get trapped in suboptimal states. Like a day trader making quick decisions.
          {' '}
          <strong className="text-green-300">🎯 Dynamic Programming:</strong> Evaluates all possible partitions 
          to find the globally optimal solution. Slower but guarantees the best possible market efficiency. 
          Like a strategic investor planning long-term. Toggle between them to see the difference!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default DualLLMBrain;

